{
  "stem": "21310.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And-- but then when the war broke out, it was so sudden we didn't even know if it was a-- a-- the real air-- the drill or the real air raid.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And it was-- it turned out it was the real air raid.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was in Warsaw in 1939, and the bombardment started almost immediately.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were incendiary bombs falling all over.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Warsaw was just in flame.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know what the percentage of the city was that was destroyed, but I think at least about 35%, 40% was destroyed by-- in the first onslaught.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "People were taken out of the of Warsaw to dig ditches, anti-tank ditches.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Labor battalions were organized, and people were digging ditches.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then the artillery was coming closer and closer, and we were being shelled.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "On ninth in [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I think on September 6 or so, an order was given for all able-bodied men, the age between, I think, 15 and 55 or 60 should leave Warsaw and go east.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Warsaw is on a-- at the Vistula River.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So that meant crossing the river and going east towards Russia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I understand that the idea was that then Warsaw could be declared, then like, an open city-- that there was no-- no men and only women and children.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So supposedly, Hitler was not supposed to bomb it and-- because it was an open city, an undefended city.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But it was incongruous because on the other hand they did prepare these ditches for, you know, for defense.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My father took his knapsack and left with thousands of other people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And matter of fact, he was sick before he left.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we had the doctor there day or two before.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
